gene-symbol: NPC1
name: NPC intracellular cholesterol transporter 1
ghr-page: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/gene/NPC1
text/text-role: function
text/html/html:p: The <i>NPC1</i> gene provides instructions for making a protein that is located within the membrane of compartments in the cell called lysosomes and endosomes, which digest and recycle materials. While the exact function of this protein is unclear, it plays a role in the movement of cholesterol and other types of fats (lipids) within cells and across cell membranes.
related-health-condition/name: Niemann-Pick disease
related-health-condition/ghr-page: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/condition/niemann-pick-disease
synonym(1): Niemann-Pick disease, type C1
synonym(2): NPC
